review_text: Amazing for photoshotgun and Good for walking, not for staying a long time, I take my friend there for taking a photos 📸

Same hour: saw red bellied woodpecker, a  male mallard duck and his wife swimming in the semi frozen swamps, a hawk, a squirrel thinking he's a flying squirrel. Wild-life bio students or zoology students would have a field trip if they visited this place, literally. I really was just hoping for funky growths in the waters and definitely found some. So much tweeting, so many birds' mating rituals and ceremonies. Highly recommended if you're looking for a little magic away from the chaos.

(Translated by Google) Natural wooded and marshy area, home to a fauna typical of the region. We came across wood frogs, dragonflies and butterflies.

Although interdicially cycling, the trails consist of a reinforced 2 m span of rock dust perfectly leveled by a large amount of embankment. This is rather contradictory to the vocation of conservation of the place, decision probably dictated to favor the access to the wheelchairs and to the services of emergencies.

Ce qui est plutôt  contradictoires avec la  vocation de conservation  du lieu, décision probablement dictée pour favoriser l'accès aux chaises roulantes et aux services d' urgences.
